# OpenCode Secrets Template
# =========================
# This file documents the required secrets for OpenCode MCP servers.
# Secrets are stored in the .secrets/ directory (git-ignored).
#
# Setup Options:
#   1. Run ./setup-secrets.sh (interactive)
#   2. Manually create each file in .secrets/
#
# File Format:
#   - Each file contains ONLY the secret value
#   - No key=value format, no quotes, no trailing newline
#   - Example: echo -n "your-api-key" > .secrets/brave-api-key
#
# Security:
#   - Directory permissions: 700 (drwx------)
#   - File permissions: 600 (-rw-------)
#   - Ensure disk encryption (FileVault on macOS) is enabled
#
# ============================================================================
# REQUIRED SECRETS
# ============================================================================

brave-api-key
  # Purpose: Brave Search API authentication
  # Used by: brave_search MCP server
  # Get from: https://brave.com/search/api/
  # Format: BSA-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

github-token
  # Purpose: GitHub API authentication
  # Used by: github MCP server (official)
  # Get from: https://github.com/settings/tokens
  # Token type: Personal Access Token (classic or fine-grained)
  # Required scopes (classic):
  #   - repo (full control of private repositories)
  #   - read:org (read organization membership)
  #   - read:user (read user profile data)
  # Format: ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

gitlab-token
  # Purpose: GitLab API authentication
  # Used by: gitlab MCP server
  # Get from: https://<your-gitlab>/-/user_settings/personal_access_tokens
  # Required scopes:
  #   - api (full API access)
  #   - read_repository (read repository content)
  # Format: glpat-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

gitlab-api-url
  # Purpose: GitLab API endpoint (for self-hosted instances)
  # Used by: gitlab MCP server
  # Format: https://gitlab.example.com/api/v4
  # Note: Keep private if using self-hosted GitLab

